    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 138200.0,
      "end_time": 141489.0,
      "text": "And would it actually help to keep people out of poverty?"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 141490.0,
      "end_time": 143860.0,
      "text": "OK, so let&#39;s dive right into the main arguments"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 143860.0,
      "end_time": 146300.0,
      "text": "for and against universal basic income."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 146300.0,
      "end_time": 147710.0,
      "text": "Giving people free money might sound"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 147710.0,
      "end_time": 149230.0,
      "text": "like a classic left-right topic"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 149230.0,
      "end_time": 151590.0,
      "text": "where liberals are for it and conservatives are against it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 151590.0,
      "end_time": 153110.0,
      "text": "but there are actually segments"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 153110.0,
      "end_time": 154990.0,
      "text": "of both groups that support it."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 154990.0,
      "end_time": 156900.0,
      "text": "Some liberals think that it&#39;s one of the best ways"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 156900.0,
      "end_time": 160700.0,
      "text": "to fight what&#39;s been a losing battle: financial inequality."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 160700.0,
      "end_time": 163170.0,
      "text": "The world&#39;s richest 1% owns half of the world&#39;s wealth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 163170.0,
      "end_time": 166750.0,
      "text": "and by 2030 it&#39;s estimated to increase to 2/3."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 166750.0,
      "end_time": 169210.0,
      "text": "Now as the poor get poorer, and artificial intelligence"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 169210.0,
      "end_time": 171570.0,
      "text": "takes more jobs, a universal basic income"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 171570.0,
      "end_time": 173769.0,
      "text": "might provide enough cash so they don&#39;t have to choose"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 173770.0,
      "end_time": 175220.0,
      "text": "between buying food for the week"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 175220.0,
      "end_time": 176750.0,
      "text": "or paying the electric bill."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 176750.0,
      "end_time": 178280.0,
      "text": "For people that still have jobs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 178280.0,
      "end_time": 180730.0,
      "text": "the extra money might allow them to pay for more education,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 180730.0,
      "end_time": 182660.0,
      "text": "or put some money away for savings."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 182660.0,
      "end_time": 184180.0,
      "text": "Now, it&#39;s important to point out"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 184180.0,
      "end_time": 186100.0,
      "text": "that the U.S. already has a welfare system"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 186100.0,
      "end_time": 187460.0,
      "text": "designed to help the poor."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 187460.0,
      "end_time": 190160.0,
      "text": "Programs like Food Stamps, federal housing assistance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 190160.0,
      "end_time": 191910.0,
      "text": "and free and low-cost health care."
